values
  ('Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser', 'dermaceutic-advanced-cleanser', 'SA-DERM-PUR-ADC-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Your serums cannot absorb properly through incompletely cleansed skin — and most cleansers either strip the barrier or leave residue behind. <strong>Advanced Cleanser does neither.</strong> The <strong>Zinc PCA reduces sebum by 42% in 30 minutes</strong>, the Xylitol complex actively prevents dryness through the cleansing process, and the amino acid surfactant system leaves skin clean, balanced, and ready to absorb. Vegan. Safe during pregnancy. Fragrance present.</p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin feels tight or stripped after cleansing</li><li>You use active serums and want maximum absorption</li><li>Your skin is oily, combination, or blemish-prone</li><li>You want a cleanser that works with your skincare routine, not against it</li><li>You are pregnant or breastfeeding — this cleanser is safe during pregnancy</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser works — the science</h3><p>Most cleansers remove dirt and makeup but leave an invisible film that blocks active ingredients from penetrating. Advanced Cleanser solves both problems at once.</p><p>The <strong>Zinc PCA</strong> molecule reduces oil production by up to 42% within 30 minutes — clinically effective for oily and blemish-prone skin without dryness. Simultaneously, a <strong>Xylitol complex</strong> derived from birch bark feeds beneficial skin bacteria and prevents the transepidermal water loss that typically accompanies thorough cleansing. The result: skin that is genuinely clean but never stripped.</p><p>The <strong>amino acid surfactant system</strong> (sodium cocoyl glutamate) matches the skin''s natural pH and leaves no residue that would impair serum absorption.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Skin feels clean, comfortable, and not tight after rinsing. <strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Oily skin visibly less shiny by midday. Pores appear cleaner. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Improved absorption of serums applied after cleansing. <strong>Ongoing:</strong> Consistent oil control and balanced skin texture.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser</h3><ol><li>Apply a small amount to damp skin morning and evening</li><li>Massage gently in circular motions for 60 seconds</li><li>Rinse thoroughly with lukewarm water</li><li>Pat dry — do not rub</li><li>Apply your serum or treatment immediately while skin is still slightly damp</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Zinc PCA</td><td>Reduces sebum production by up to 42% in 30 minutes — clinically proven oil control without dryness</td></tr><tr><td>Xylitol Complex</td><td>Feeds beneficial skin microbiome bacteria and prevents moisture loss during cleansing</td></tr><tr><td>Amino Acid Surfactants</td><td>Gentle pH-matched cleansing that removes impurities without stripping the skin barrier</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Cleanser is the most commonly underestimated step in a skincare routine. I recommend Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser as the starting point for virtually every patient in my clinic, regardless of skin type or concern. If your cleanser is stripping your barrier, every active you apply afterwards is fighting an uphill battle. Get the first step right and everything else performs better.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I noticed my SPF and serum were absorbing so much better within the first week. My skin just feels different — clean but not dry.</td><td>I was sceptical about spending this much on a cleanser. Now I won''t go back. My oiliness is genuinely under control by midday.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee recommended this as step one of my routine. Everything else in my routine works better since switching to this cleanser.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I use this cleanser if I have sensitive skin?</td><td>Yes — the amino acid surfactant system is among the gentlest available and is well-tolerated by sensitive skin. The fragrance in the formula is the only potential sensitiser; if you are highly fragrance-sensitive, consult Dr. Bangalee before use.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it safe during pregnancy?</td><td>Yes. Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser is safe during pregnancy and breastfeeding. It contains no retinoids, high-dose AHAs, or other actives contraindicated in pregnancy.</td></tr><tr><td>How is this different from Foamer 15?</td><td>Advanced Cleanser is the gentler, everyday cleanser for all skin types. Foamer 15 contains 15% Glycolic Acid and is a resurfacing cleanser. Many patients use Advanced Cleanser in the morning and Foamer 15 in the evening.</td></tr><tr><td>How long does one tube last?</td><td>Used twice daily, one 100ml tube typically lasts 6–8 weeks.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic or Activ Retinol (evening)</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Protect</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 (morning)</p></td></tr></table>', 71500, 71500, true, ARRAY['all skin types', 'barrier-safe', 'cleansing gel', 'daily cleanser', 'Dermaceutic', 'gentle cleanser', 'Purify', 'sensitive skin']),
  ('Dermaceutic Activabiome', 'dermaceutic-activabiome', 'SA-DERM-RES-ACT-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Breakouts keep returning because most acne products treat the symptom, not the cause. <strong>Activabiome works overnight to rebalance your skin''s microbiome</strong> — using <strong>7% Glycolic Acid and 1% Salicylic Acid</strong> to clear pores, a marine algae-derived complex to inhibit bacteria and control sebum, and a <strong>2% Microbiota Regulator</strong> to restore the biological conditions that keep skin clear long-term. <strong>Not for use during pregnancy.</strong></p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Activabiome right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your acne or blemishes keep returning despite regular treatment</li><li>You want to address the microbiome imbalance that drives persistent breakouts</li><li>You have oily or combination skin prone to congestion and blackheads</li><li>You want a comprehensive overnight treatment combining exfoliation, anti-bacterial, and microbiome support</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Activabiome works — the science</h3><p>The skin microbiome — the community of bacteria and microorganisms living on the skin surface — plays a fundamental role in acne formation. When balanced, beneficial bacteria keep Cutibacterium acnes under control. When disrupted by over-cleansing or harsh actives, C. acnes proliferates and blemishes recur.</p><p>Most anti-acne treatments kill bacteria but ignore the underlying microbiome balance — which is why blemishes return as soon as treatment stops. Activabiome addresses both levels. The <strong>7% Glycolic Acid + 1% Salicylic Acid combination</strong> delivers comprehensive exfoliation: Glycolic Acid resurfaces the skin surface, while Salicylic Acid (being oil-soluble) penetrates into pores to dissolve sebum plugs and blackheads from within. The <strong>marine algae complex</strong> inhibits C. acnes activity and controls sebum. The <strong>2% Microbiota Regulator</strong> restores the biological balance on the skin surface — creating conditions where beneficial bacteria thrive and C. acnes cannot dominate.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Skin feels cleaner and pores less congested. Initial mild purging possible. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Reduction in new blemish formation. Blackheads visibly reduced. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Significantly fewer breakouts. Skin clearer and more balanced. <strong>Month 3+:</strong> Long-term microbiome rebalancing — skin remains clear with consistent use.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Activabiome</h3><ol><li>Apply in the evening after cleansing</li><li>Apply a thin layer to the entire face, focusing on congested areas</li><li>Allow to absorb — mild tingling from AHA/BHA combination is normal</li><li>Follow with Hyal Ceutic moisturiser if needed</li><li>Apply SPF50+ every morning — AHA use increases UV sensitivity</li><li>Introduce gradually — begin 3 evenings per week and increase as skin adjusts</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>7% Glycolic Acid</td><td>Resurfaces skin surface, removes dead cell buildup, and clears follicular debris</td></tr><tr><td>1% Salicylic Acid (BHA)</td><td>Oil-soluble — penetrates into pores to dissolve sebum plugs and blackheads from within</td></tr><tr><td>Marine algae complex</td><td>Inhibits C. acnes bacteria and controls sebum production at the sebaceous gland</td></tr><tr><td>2% Microbiota Regulator</td><td>Restores skin microbiome balance — creates conditions where beneficial bacteria prevent long-term C. acnes dominance</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Activabiome addresses the underlying microbiome disruption that causes recurring acne. I recommend it for patients who have persistent blemishes despite good skincare habits — the microbiome component means results are sustained rather than temporary. Combining Activabiome home care with Dermapen or chemical peel clinic visits gives patients both the structural correction and the biological balance they need for long-term clear skin.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have had recurring acne since my 20s. Three months on Activabiome and I have had fewer breakouts than at any point in the past ten years.</td><td>My pores were cleaner and less congested within the first two weeks. By week six the improvement in my blemishes was dramatic.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee combined this with an in-clinic chemical peel. The combination cleared what years of different products could not.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>What is the skin microbiome and why does it matter for acne?</td><td>The skin microbiome is the community of microorganisms that live on your skin surface. A balanced microbiome keeps acne-causing bacteria in check. When disrupted, C. acnes dominates and blemishes become persistent. Restoring that balance is the key insight behind Activabiome.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use Activabiome if I am on prescription acne treatment?</td><td>Consult Dr. Bangalee before combining with prescription actives — certain combinations require careful management to deliver the best results.</td></tr><tr><td>Is Activabiome suitable during pregnancy?</td><td>The AHA and BHA concentrations mean Activabiome is not recommended during pregnancy. Consult Dr. Bangalee for pregnancy-safe alternatives.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Activabiome</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</p></td></tr></table>', 113500, 113500, true, ARRAY['barrier repair', 'Dermaceutic', 'microbiome', 'post-treatment', 'probiotic', 'recovery cream', 'Restore', 'sensitive skin']),
  ('Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic', 'dermaceutic-hyal-ceutic', 'SA-DERM-STI-HYC-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Oily skin is often dehydrated skin — producing excess oil to compensate for the moisture it lacks. <strong>Hyal Ceutic''s 5.5% dual-weight Hyaluronic Acid system</strong> hydrates at both the surface and deeper dermal layers simultaneously, while <strong>10% Aloe Vera Gel</strong> soothes and <strong>1% Jojoba Oil</strong> seals without congestion. Lightweight enough for oily and combination skin. Non-comedogenic. Fragrance free. Vegan. Safe during pregnancy.</p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin is oily or combination but still feels tight or dry</li><li>Heavier moisturisers feel congesting or cause breakouts</li><li>You use retinols or AHAs and need a hydrating buffer</li><li>You want fragrance-free hydration safe during pregnancy</li><li>You are looking for a non-comedogenic moisturiser that will not block pores</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic works — the science</h3><p>The misconception that oily skin does not need moisture is one of the most damaging beliefs in skincare. Oily skin frequently overproduces sebum precisely because it is dehydrated — the sebaceous glands compensate for water loss by producing more oil. Adding moisture to oily skin can actually reduce oiliness over time.</p><p>Hyal Ceutic uses a <strong>5.5% dual-weight Hyaluronic Acid system</strong> — high-molecular-weight HA sits on the skin surface and prevents transepidermal water loss, while low-molecular-weight HA penetrates deeper to hydrate at the dermal level. <strong>10% Aloe Vera Gel</strong> provides immediate soothing for skin reactive from AHA or retinol use. <strong>1% Jojoba Oil</strong> provides a lipid seal structurally similar to the skin''s own sebum — absorbs cleanly without congestion.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Skin feels hydrated and comfortable without heaviness or greasiness. <strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Skin less reactive to other actives. Tightness after cleansing resolved. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Oiliness may begin to moderate as dehydration signal reduces. <strong>Week 6+:</strong> Improved texture and more balanced oil production.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic</h3><ol><li>Apply morning and/or evening after cleansing and any treatment serums</li><li>Apply to slightly damp skin — Hyaluronic Acid binds ambient moisture for improved results</li><li>Pat gently across face and neck — do not rub</li><li>Allow to absorb before applying SPF (morning) or additional treatment (evening)</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>5.5% Dual-weight Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Hydrates at both surface and dermal level — prevents water loss while plumping skin from within</td></tr><tr><td>10% Aloe Vera Gel</td><td>Soothes inflammation and calms reactive skin — essential buffer for AHA and retinol users</td></tr><tr><td>1% Jojoba Oil</td><td>Lightweight lipid seal that mimics skin''s own sebum — absorbs cleanly without clogging pores</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Hyal Ceutic is my most-recommended moisturiser for patients with oily and combination skin following an active skincare programme. One of the most common causes of poor tolerance to actives is an impaired moisture barrier — Hyal Ceutic restores that barrier without adding weight or comedogenic risk. It is also the moisturiser I recommend during pregnancy for patients who want safe, effective hydration.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have oily skin and avoided moisturiser for years. Dr. Bangalee convinced me to try Hyal Ceutic. Within a month, my skin is less oily AND less tight. I had no idea dehydration was causing my oil problem.</td><td>This is the only moisturiser that doesn''t break me out. It absorbs completely, leaves no residue, and my skin looks better since I started using it.</td><td>I use this after my retinol every evening and it has completely eliminated the flakiness and irritation I used to experience.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Will Hyal Ceutic make oily skin even oilier?</td><td>No. Hyal Ceutic is lightweight, non-comedogenic, and absorbs without leaving residue. For many oily skin patients, properly hydrating the skin reduces oiliness over time because the dehydration signal driving sebum overproduction is removed.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it safe during pregnancy?</td><td>Yes. Hyal Ceutic is fragrance-free, vegan, and safe during pregnancy and breastfeeding.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use this with retinol?</td><td>Absolutely — Hyal Ceutic is the ideal partner for any retinol product. Apply retinol first, allow to absorb for 10–15 minutes, then apply Hyal Ceutic as your moisturiser.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser or Foamer 15</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat</p><p>Dermaceutic Activabiome or Activ Retinol</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 (morning)</p></td></tr></table>', 113500, 113500, true, ARRAY['dehydrated skin', 'Dermaceutic', 'dry skin', 'hyaluronic acid', 'hydrating cream', 'moisturiser', 'plumping', 'Stimulate']),
  ('Dermaceutic Activ Retinol 1.0', 'dermaceutic-activ-retinol-10', 'SA-DERM-REN-AR1-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Maximum-strength home-use retinol for patients who have built tolerance through the graduated Dermaceutic programme. The newly reformulated <strong>triple-retinol technology</strong> combines <strong>0.3% Pure Retinol</strong> with <strong>1% Retinol Boost</strong> — a next-generation bio-retinoid from marine algae — and a <strong>1% ceramide complex</strong> for barrier support. Clinically significant anti-ageing results. Evening use only. <strong>Contains Vitamin A. Not for use during pregnancy.</strong></p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Activ Retinol 1.0 right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have been using retinol and your skin has built full tolerance through the graduated programme</li><li>You want the most powerful home-use retinol formulation available</li><li>You have established fine lines, wrinkles, or uneven tone you want to address aggressively</li><li>Your skin is not sensitive or reactive — you have been on a clinical skincare programme</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding</li><li>You have been recommended this strength by Dr. Bangalee</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Activ Retinol 1.0 works — the science</h3><p>Retinol is the most clinically validated anti-ageing active in cosmetic skincare. Decades of research confirm its ability to stimulate collagen synthesis, accelerate cellular turnover, and improve photodamage, fine lines, uneven tone, and skin texture.</p><p>Activ Retinol 1.0 uses the reformulated <strong>triple-retinol technology</strong>. <strong>0.3% Pure Retinol</strong> delivers the primary anti-ageing activity — stimulating collagen synthesis and cellular renewal. <strong>1% Retinol Boost</strong> is a proprietary bio-retinoid from marine algae that acts on the same retinoid receptors as Pure Retinol, enhancing and extending its activity. The <strong>1% ceramide complex</strong> reinforces the skin barrier simultaneously — reducing peeling, dryness, and irritation at this maximum concentration.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Possible mild skin purging — expected at this concentration. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Skin texture visibly smoother; fine lines begin to soften. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Significant improvement in skin firmness, tone, and fine lines. <strong>Month 3–6:</strong> Clinically significant anti-ageing results — collagen synthesis benefits compound over time.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Activ Retinol 1.0</h3><ol><li>Evening use only — retinol degrades in sunlight</li><li>Cleanse skin thoroughly first</li><li>Apply a thin layer to completely dry skin — wet skin increases penetration rate and may cause irritation</li><li>A pea-sized amount is sufficient for the entire face</li><li>Wait 20–30 minutes before applying moisturiser (Hyal Ceutic)</li><li>Apply SPF50+ (K Ceutic) every morning without exception</li><li>Begin 2 evenings per week and increase to nightly as skin demonstrates full tolerance</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>0.3% Pure Retinol</td><td>Gold-standard anti-ageing retinol — stimulates collagen synthesis, accelerates cellular renewal, corrects photodamage</td></tr><tr><td>1% Retinol Boost (marine bio-retinoid)</td><td>Next-generation retinoid that enhances and extends Pure Retinol activity at the same receptor sites</td></tr><tr><td>1% Ceramide Complex</td><td>Reinforces skin barrier to improve tolerance and reduce dryness at maximum retinol concentration</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Activ Retinol 1.0 is the conclusion of the graduated Dermaceutic retinol programme — 0.1 for introduction, 0.3 for establishment, 0.5 for progression, and 1.0 for clinical results. I only recommend this strength to patients who have genuinely built tolerance through the lower concentrations. For the right patient at the right stage, this is one of the most effective anti-ageing actives available for home use. The reformulated triple-retinol technology is a genuine advance.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I worked my way up from 0.1 to 1.0 over about a year as Dr. Bangalee recommended. At 1.0 the results are genuinely dramatic — my skin looks ten years younger.</td><td>The ceramide complex means my skin is not dry or irritated at this strength. It took about six weeks to see the full effect but it is absolutely worth the patience.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee set me up on this as a home-care option. Very impressed — this is clinical skincare at a proper level.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I start with Activ Retinol 1.0 if I have never used retinol before?</td><td>No — starting at 1.0 without preparation commonly causes significant barrier disruption and sensitisation. Begin with Activ Retinol 0.1 and progress through the graduated programme.</td></tr><tr><td>What is the difference between the four Activ Retinol strengths?</td><td>0.1 is the introduction for first-time retinol users. 0.3 establishes a retinol routine with visible results. 0.5 progresses to meaningful anti-ageing activity. 1.0 is the maximum-strength clinical formulation for patients with full retinol tolerance.</td></tr><tr><td>How long before I see results?</td><td>Meaningful improvement in fine lines and skin density typically requires 8–12 weeks of consistent use. Texture improvement and tone correction are often visible sooner.</td></tr><tr><td>Why is it not for use during pregnancy?</td><td>All retinoid products are contraindicated during pregnancy and breastfeeding. Discontinue when trying to conceive.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser or Foamer 15</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Activ Retinol 1.0</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic or Hyal Ceutic Redens+</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</p></td></tr></table>', 168500, 168500, true, ARRAY['1% retinol', 'anti-ageing serum', 'cell renewal', 'Dermaceutic', 'retinol', 'skin texture', 'Stimulate', 'wrinkles']),
  ('Dermaceutic Radiance Mask', 'dermaceutic-radiance-mask', 'SA-DERM-PRE-RAD-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Dull, uneven complexion builds gradually — and a standard cleanser won''t reverse it. <strong>Radiance''s new improved formula corrects this with a 5-active brightening complex</strong> including Kojic Acid, Alpha-Arbutin, Niacinamide, and the innovative <strong>Hydroxyphenoxy Propionic Acid</strong> — which uniquely blocks both melanin production AND its transfer to skin cells. Leave-on evening cream. <strong>100% of volunteers confirmed a more even, luminous complexion in 28 days.</strong> Not for use during pregnancy.</p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Radiance Mask right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your complexion looks dull, flat, or uneven</li><li>You have mild-to-moderate pigmentation or uneven skin tone</li><li>You want a leave-on brightening treatment you can use regularly</li><li>You want clinical actives backed by consumer testing (100% efficacy confirmed at 28 days)</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Radiance Mask works — the science</h3><p>Radiance Mask earns its name through clinical formulation. The new improved formula uses a <strong>5-active brightening complex</strong> that addresses pigmentation and luminosity through multiple simultaneous pathways.</p><p><strong>Kojic Acid</strong> is a naturally-derived tyrosinase inhibitor — it blocks the primary enzyme responsible for converting tyrosine to melanin. <strong>Alpha-Arbutin</strong> is a highly stable melanin synthesis inhibitor derived from the bearberry plant. <strong>Niacinamide</strong> (Vitamin B3) uniquely inhibits the transfer of melanin from melanocytes to keratinocytes. The innovative <strong>Hydroxyphenoxy Propionic Acid</strong> is the standout active — it simultaneously blocks melanin production AND its transfer, delivering double-pathway brightening activity in a single molecule. In consumer testing, <strong>100% of volunteers confirmed a more even, luminous complexion in 28 days</strong>.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Skin appears more luminous. Surface dullness reducing. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Uneven tone visibly improving. Existing pigmentation beginning to lighten — confirmed by 100% of consumer testers at 28 days. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Progressive brightening with consistent use.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Radiance Mask</h3><ol><li>Apply in the evening after cleansing</li><li>Apply an even layer across the entire face and neck</li><li>Leave on overnight — do not rinse</li><li>Follow with Hyal Ceutic moisturiser if needed</li><li>Apply SPF50+ every morning — UV exposure will inhibit the brightening effect</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Kojic Acid</td><td>Naturally-derived tyrosinase inhibitor — blocks melanin production at source</td></tr><tr><td>Alpha-Arbutin</td><td>Highly stable melanin synthesis inhibitor — progressive brightening of existing pigmentation</td></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide (Vitamin B3)</td><td>Inhibits melanin transfer from pigment cells to skin cells — a unique brightening pathway</td></tr><tr><td>Hydroxyphenoxy Propionic Acid</td><td>Innovative dual-action active — blocks both melanin production AND transfer simultaneously</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Radiance Mask is the brightening product I recommend for patients who want consistent, progressive improvement in skin tone. The 100% consumer efficacy result at 28 days gives me confidence in recommending it broadly. The inclusion of Hydroxyphenoxy Propionic Acid in the reformulated version makes it meaningfully more effective than the previous formula. I often recommend this alongside K Ceutic SPF 50 for patients whose primary concern is dull, uneven complexion.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>Within three weeks my skin looked noticeably brighter and my foundation goes on more evenly. This product does exactly what it says.</td><td>I have been using Radiance Mask every evening for two months. My pigmentation has faded steadily and my overall skin tone is much more uniform.</td><td>The 28-day claim is accurate — I photographed my skin at the start and at day 28. The difference is genuinely visible.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Is Radiance Mask a physical mask I rinse off?</td><td>No — despite the name, Radiance Mask is a leave-on overnight treatment cream, not a rinse-off mask. Apply it as your evening treatment and leave it on throughout the night.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use Radiance Mask and Mela Cream together?</td><td>These are both brightening treatments — use one in the evening. Mela Cream is the more intensive treatment for established pigmentation. Radiance Mask is appropriate for general brightening and maintenance. Dr. Bangalee can advise which is more appropriate.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser or Foamer 15</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Radiance Mask</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic (if needed)</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 (essential)</p></td></tr></table>', 113500, 113500, true, ARRAY['antioxidant', 'brightening mask', 'Dermaceutic', 'glow', 'Prevent', 'radiance', 'Vitamin C mask', 'weekly treatment']),
  ('Dermaceutic Dual Plus', 'dermaceutic-dual-plus', 'SA-DERM-TAR-DUP-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Oily, blemish-prone skin with dark marks is the dual challenge most skincare fails to address properly — anti-acne products ignore pigmentation, and brightening products ignore active blemishes. <strong>Dual+ solves both simultaneously</strong> with a unique combination of <strong>two azelaic acid forms, Hexylresorcinol and Alpha-Arbutin</strong> — targeting bacteria, sebum, pore congestion and melanin production in a single evening treatment. <strong>Not for use during pregnancy.</strong></p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Dual+ right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have oily or acne-prone skin AND dark marks or uneven tone simultaneously</li><li>You have tried acne products that cleared blemishes but left dark marks behind</li><li>You want a single product that addresses both active blemishes and existing pigmentation</li><li>You have post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (dark marks from previous spots)</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Dual+ works — the science</h3><p>Post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation — the dark marks left by healed blemishes — coexists with ongoing blemish formation, meaning patients need both anti-acne and brightening activity simultaneously. Most products are formulated for one or the other.</p><p>Dual+ addresses both pathways in a single formulation. The <strong>two azelaic acid forms</strong> deliver anti-bacterial, anti-inflammatory, and anti-comedogenic activity — reducing active blemishes, controlling sebum, and preventing new comedone formation. Simultaneously, <strong>Hexylresorcinol</strong> and <strong>Alpha-Arbutin</strong> deliver complementary brightening activity — Hexylresorcinol fades existing pigmentation while Alpha-Arbutin prevents new dark mark formation after blemishes heal.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 2–3:</strong> Active blemishes reduce in severity. Pores appear less congested. <strong>Week 4–6:</strong> New blemish formation reducing. Existing dark marks beginning to lighten. <strong>Week 8–12:</strong> Progressive fading of post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation. Skin tone becoming more uniform.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Dual+</h3><ol><li>Apply in the evening after cleansing</li><li>Apply a thin, even layer to affected areas or entire face</li><li>Allow to absorb before applying moisturiser (Hyal Ceutic)</li><li>Apply SPF50+ every morning</li><li>Introduce gradually — begin 3 evenings per week and increase to nightly as skin adjusts</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Dual azelaic acid complex</td><td>Anti-bacterial, anti-inflammatory, anti-comedogenic — reduces active blemishes and controls sebum</td></tr><tr><td>Hexylresorcinol</td><td>Powerful tyrosinase inhibitor — fades existing post-inflammatory dark marks</td></tr><tr><td>Alpha-Arbutin</td><td>Prevents new melanin formation after blemishes heal — breaks the cycle of spot-mark-spot-mark</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Dual+ fills a genuine gap — oily, blemish-prone skin with post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation is extremely common, particularly in darker skin tones, and until products like Dual+ existed we had to layer two separate evening treatments. A single well-formulated product that does both is a significant practical advance. I recommend this for acne patients as a bridge treatment: in-clinic acne management combined with Dual+ home care.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have been dealing with spots AND dark marks for years. Dual+ is the first product that has addressed both at the same time.</td><td>The azelaic acid controls my oiliness without drying my skin, and the brightening actives are working on my PIH. My skin is the clearest it has been in five years.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee prescribed this alongside in-clinic acne treatment. Fewer new spots AND the old marks are fading.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I use Dual+ if my skin is sensitive?</td><td>Azelaic acid is generally well-tolerated — it is one of the few anti-acne actives suitable for sensitive skin. Some initial mild tingling is normal. Introduce gradually.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use Dual+ with retinol?</td><td>Use on alternate evenings — not on the same night. Dr. Bangalee will advise the appropriate combined protocol for your specific concern.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Foamer 15 or Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Dual+</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</p></td></tr></table>', 176400, 176400, true, ARRAY['AHA BHA', 'dark spot corrector', 'Dermaceutic', 'exfoliation', 'pigmentation', 'post-treatment', 'Target', 'uneven skin tone']),
  ('Dermaceutic C25', 'dermaceutic-c25', 'SA-DERM-PRE-C25-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>If your Vitamin C serum is not delivering visible brightening, the issue is formulation stability. <strong>C25 Cream uses 25% Ascorbyl Silanol</strong> — a silicone-bound Vitamin C form with superior skin penetration and stability — combined with <strong>Vitamins A, B5 and E, plus Polyphenols</strong>, in a fragrance-free morning cream. A morning antioxidant treatment that visibly increases luminosity and reduces fine lines with consistent use. <strong>Contains Vitamin A — not for use during pregnancy.</strong></p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic C25 right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have tried Vitamin C serums that oxidised quickly or delivered no visible results</li><li>You want a stable, high-concentration Vitamin C in a cream format</li><li>Your skin is dull, uneven, or shows early signs of UV-induced ageing</li><li>You want a morning antioxidant treatment that provides genuine photoprotection support</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding (contains Vitamin A)</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic C25 works — the science</h3><p>Vitamin C is one of the most clinically validated antioxidants in skincare — but it is also one of the most unstable. L-Ascorbic Acid (the most active form) oxidises rapidly on exposure to air and light. Most Vitamin C products are already partially degraded by the time the consumer uses them.</p><p>C25 uses <strong>Ascorbyl Silanol</strong> — a silicone-bound derivative of Vitamin C that is significantly more stable than L-Ascorbic Acid and demonstrates superior skin penetration. At <strong>25% concentration</strong>, this delivers a clinically meaningful dose of Vitamin C activity at the dermal level. Combined with <strong>Vitamins A, E, B5 and Polyphenols</strong>, C25 delivers a comprehensive antioxidant network — multiple pathways are activated simultaneously, providing broader protection against oxidative stress than single-antioxidant products.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Skin appears more luminous; dullness visibly reduced. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Uneven tone begins to even. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Progressive reduction in fine lines and improvement in skin density. <strong>Ongoing:</strong> Cumulative antioxidant protection against daily UV and environmental oxidative damage.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic C25</h3><ol><li>Apply in the morning only — antioxidants work best before UV exposure</li><li>Cleanse skin first</li><li>Apply a small amount and spread evenly across face and neck</li><li>Allow to absorb for 2–3 minutes</li><li>Follow with K Ceutic SPF 50</li><li>Do not use in the evening — Vitamin A content means sun exposure must be avoided after application</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>25% Ascorbyl Silanol</td><td>Stable, high-penetration Vitamin C that delivers genuine brightening and antioxidant activity without oxidation</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin A (Retinyl Palmitate)</td><td>Supports cellular renewal and collagen formation — synergistic anti-ageing effect</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin E</td><td>Regenerates oxidised Vitamin C to extend its antioxidant activity</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin B5 (Panthenol)</td><td>Soothes and promotes skin healing — improves texture and tolerance</td></tr><tr><td>Polyphenols</td><td>Additional antioxidant and anti-inflammatory protection against UV and environmental damage</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>C25 with Ascorbyl Silanol gives me confidence that the concentration stated on the label is actually active when the patient applies it. I recommend C25 as the cornerstone morning treatment for patients who want to address dullness and UV-induced ageing while providing daily antioxidant protection. Pair it with K Ceutic SPF 50 for the most effective morning photoprotection protocol available in home-use skincare.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have used Vitamin C serums for years and none made a visible difference. C25 has changed my opinion entirely. Within three weeks my skin was noticeably brighter.</td><td>The cream texture absorbs beautifully. My skin glows in a natural way — not shiny, just healthy looking.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee prescribed this alongside K Ceutic after my chemical peel. My skin tone has never been more even.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Why does C25 use Ascorbyl Silanol instead of L-Ascorbic Acid?</td><td>L-Ascorbic Acid is the most biologically active form of Vitamin C but oxidises rapidly. Ascorbyl Silanol delivers comparable activity with far superior stability, meaning the product remains effective throughout its shelf life.</td></tr><tr><td>Why is it not for use during pregnancy?</td><td>C25 contains Vitamin A (Retinyl Palmitate). All Vitamin A derivatives are generally avoided during pregnancy as a precaution.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use C25 in the same routine as retinol?</td><td>Yes — use C25 in the morning and retinol in the evening. This is the classic Dermaceutic protocol: antioxidant + SPF in the morning, retinol + moisturiser in the evening.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse AM</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat AM</p><p>Dermaceutic C25</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Activ Retinol + Hyal Ceutic</p></td></tr></table>', 117000, 117000, true, ARRAY['25% Vitamin C', 'anti-ageing', 'antioxidant', 'brightening', 'collagen', 'Dermaceutic', 'Prevent', 'Vitamin C cream']),
  ('Dermaceutic Foamer 15', 'dermaceutic-foamer-15', 'SA-DERM-PUR-F15-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Most cleansers leave an invisible film that blocks your serums from working. <strong>Foamer 15 dissolves it completely</strong> — using <strong>15% Glycolic Acid</strong> (pharmaceutical grade, &gt;99.9% pure) to resurface while it rinses, removing dead cell buildup, unclogging pores, and priming your skin to absorb everything that follows. The clinical-grade cleanser every active skincare routine needs as its foundation.</p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Foamer 15 right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin feels dull, rough, or has uneven texture</li><li>You use serums and actives but feel they have stopped working</li><li>Your pores look congested or enlarged</li><li>You have oily or combination skin</li><li>You want a clinical AHA cleanser as part of a resurfacing routine</li><li>You have already used gentler AHA products and are ready to step up</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Foamer 15 works — the science</h3><p>Glycolic Acid is the smallest alpha-hydroxy acid molecule — small enough to penetrate the stratum corneum and dissolve the bonds holding dead skin cells to the surface. At <strong>15% pharmaceutical-grade concentration (&gt;99.9% pure)</strong>, Foamer 15 delivers clinical exfoliation in every wash.</p><p>Unlike leave-on AHA treatments, a rinse-off application means the acid is active only during contact time — effective but self-limiting. The foaming action spreads the acid evenly across the skin surface, ensuring consistent exfoliation. Dead cell buildup is removed, pore congestion is cleared, and the skin surface is optimally primed for absorption of serums applied after cleansing.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>After first use:</strong> Skin feels immediately smoother with a mild tingle during application. <strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Improved serum absorption. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Texture noticeably smoother, pores appearing cleaner. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Progressive brightening and significant texture refinement.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Foamer 15</h3><ol><li>Use in the evening only — AHA increases photosensitivity; always apply SPF the following morning</li><li>Wet face with lukewarm water</li><li>Gently massage over entire face and neck for 30–60 seconds</li><li>Rinse thoroughly</li><li>A mild tingling sensation is normal — do not leave on longer than recommended</li><li>Follow with your evening treatment serum and moisturiser</li><li>Introduce gradually — begin every other evening, increasing to nightly as skin adjusts</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>15% Glycolic Acid (pharmaceutical grade &gt;99.9% pure)</td><td>Dissolves dead cell bonds, clears pore congestion, resurfaces skin texture, and maximises serum absorption</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Foamer 15 is the clinical cleanser I recommend to patients who are serious about their skincare results. The pharmaceutical-grade Glycolic Acid concentration delivers genuine resurfacing in every wash. For patients who have reached a plateau with their current routine, switching to Foamer 15 in the evening often restores visible progress within weeks.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>My skin has never been smoother. After two weeks I noticed my vitamin C serum finally seemed to be working — turns out my old cleanser was leaving a film that blocked everything.</td><td>I was nervous about using glycolic acid in a cleanser but the tingling is very mild and my skin adjusted within a week. The texture improvement is real and noticeable.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee recommended this when my skin felt like nothing was working. Within a month, the results were back. This is now a permanent part of my routine.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Will Foamer 15 make my skin dry or irritated?</td><td>Some initial sensitivity is normal — begin every other evening and increase frequency gradually. If irritation persists, reduce frequency or consult Dr. Bangalee.</td></tr><tr><td>Do I need to use SPF if I am rinsing it off at night?</td><td>Yes. AHA use increases photosensitivity even with rinse-off formulations. SPF50+ every morning is non-negotiable when using Foamer 15.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use Foamer 15 with retinol?</td><td>Use on alternating evenings rather than the same night, particularly during the introduction phase. Consult Dr. Bangalee for guidance on combining these actives.</td></tr><tr><td>Is Foamer 15 suitable during pregnancy?</td><td>High-concentration AHA cleansers are generally not recommended during pregnancy. Please consult your healthcare provider before use.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse (evening)</p><p>Dermaceutic Foamer 15</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat</p><p>Dermaceutic Light Ceutic or Activ Retinol</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Protect</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 (morning)</p></td></tr></table>', 93000, 93000, true, ARRAY['acne-prone skin', 'AHA', 'clogged pores', 'Dermaceutic', 'exfoliating cleanser', 'glycolic acid', 'oily skin', 'Purify']),
  ('Dermaceutic Light Ceutic', 'dermaceutic-light-ceutic', 'SA-DERM-STI-LIC-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Dull, uneven skin tone is caused by accumulated dead cells slowing the surface renewal cycle. <strong>Light Ceutic accelerates that cycle</strong> using pharmaceutical-grade Glycolic Acid (&gt;99.9% pure) delivered through a <strong>lamellar phospholipid emulsifier</strong> that drives it significantly deeper than standard AHA creams — restoring luminosity, smoothing texture, and fading discolouration while you sleep. Evening use only. <strong>Contains Vitamin A — not for use during pregnancy.</strong></p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Light Ceutic right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin looks dull, flat, or lacks its natural glow</li><li>You have uneven skin tone, fine lines, or rough texture</li><li>You want a leave-on AHA treatment that delivers genuine resurfacing overnight</li><li>You are comfortable with active skincare and ready for a clinical-grade exfoliant</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding (contains Vitamin A)</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Light Ceutic works — the science</h3><p>The skin renews itself through desquamation — old surface cells shed and new cells emerge from below. As we age, this process slows. Dead cells accumulate on the surface, creating the dull, uneven complexion that characterises photo-aged skin.</p><p>Light Ceutic uses <strong>pharmaceutical-grade Glycolic Acid (&gt;99.9% pure)</strong> to accelerate desquamation by dissolving the bonds holding old dead cells to the surface. What distinguishes it from standard AHA creams is the delivery system: a <strong>lamellar phospholipid emulsifier</strong> carries the Glycolic Acid significantly deeper into the stratum corneum than standard cream bases allow. <strong>Vitamin A</strong> works in synergy — Glycolic Acid clears the surface while Vitamin A stimulates cellular renewal from below.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Skin feels smoother to touch in the morning. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Visible improvement in luminosity and texture. Fine lines begin to soften. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Progressive correction of discolouration and uneven tone. Skin appears genuinely renewed.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Light Ceutic</h3><ol><li>Apply in the evening only — Glycolic Acid increases photosensitivity; always apply SPF the following morning</li><li>Cleanse skin thoroughly first</li><li>Apply a thin, even layer to face and neck</li><li>A mild tingling sensation is normal for 10–15 minutes after application</li><li>Allow to absorb — do not rinse off</li><li>Follow with Hyal Ceutic moisturiser if needed</li><li>Introduce gradually — begin 2–3 times per week and increase as skin adjusts</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Pharmaceutical-grade Glycolic Acid (&gt;99.9% pure)</td><td>Accelerates cellular turnover by dissolving dead cell bonds — restores luminosity and smooths texture</td></tr><tr><td>Lamellar phospholipid delivery system</td><td>Carries Glycolic Acid deeper than standard cream bases — clinical penetration in a home-use product</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin A</td><td>Stimulates cellular renewal from below — synergistic anti-ageing effect with surface exfoliation</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Light Ceutic is the leave-on resurfacing product I recommend for patients who want to maintain the luminosity improvement they experience after an in-clinic chemical peel. The phospholipid delivery system is what makes it genuinely clinical rather than cosmetic — the Glycolic Acid actually reaches the depth where it needs to work.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>After my first in-clinic peel I wanted to maintain the results at home. Light Ceutic has kept my skin bright and clear in a way it never did before.</td><td>My skin texture has transformed over three months of consistent use. People ask if I have had a treatment.</td><td>I was nervous about a leave-on AHA overnight but introduced it slowly as advised. My skin adapted completely and the brightening effect is remarkable.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>How much tingling is normal?</td><td>Mild to moderate tingling for 10–15 minutes is expected. Significant burning or prolonged discomfort is not normal — rinse with cool water and reduce frequency. Consult Dr. Bangalee if irritation persists.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use Light Ceutic and retinol?</td><td>Use on alternating evenings — Light Ceutic one night, retinol the next. This is a highly effective combination for comprehensive skin renewal.</td></tr><tr><td>Why is Light Ceutic not for use during pregnancy?</td><td>Light Ceutic contains Vitamin A. All Vitamin A derivatives are avoided during pregnancy as a precaution.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Foamer 15 or Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Light Ceutic</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic (if needed)</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</p></td></tr></table>', 111300, 111300, true, ARRAY['dark spots', 'Dermaceutic', 'glycolic acid', 'night cream', 'phytic acid', 'pigmentation', 'Stimulate', 'unifying cream', 'Vitamin C']),
  ('Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50', 'dermaceutic-k-ceutic-spf-50', 'SA-DERM-RES-KCE-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>Most SPF creams protect your skin from the sun. <strong>K Ceutic SPF 50 also actively repairs UV-induced skin damage every day you wear it</strong> — combining a hybrid mineral and chemical filter system with the proprietary <strong>K Complex</strong> (Vitamin K, growth factor precursors, and repair enzymes) to correct discolouration and restore luminosity as it shields. The SPF Dr. Bangalee prescribes after every clinical treatment.</p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 right for you?</h3><ul><li>You want SPF protection that also actively improves your skin</li><li>You have post-treatment skin that needs daily SPF as part of your recovery protocol</li><li>You have discolouration, uneven tone, or UV damage you want to correct over time</li><li>You have completed a chemical peel, Dermapen, or pigmentation treatment</li><li>You want an SPF that sits comfortably under makeup</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 works — the science</h3><p>Standard SPF products form a protective barrier against UV radiation — and nothing more. K Ceutic SPF 50 delivers protection and active correction simultaneously through the proprietary <strong>K Complex</strong> — Vitamin K (which reduces discolouration and vascular irregularity), growth factor precursors (which stimulate cellular repair), and repair enzymes (which correct UV-induced DNA damage).</p><p>The hybrid filter system combines both <strong>mineral</strong> (physical) and <strong>chemical</strong> UV filters — mineral filters provide immediate broad-spectrum protection, while chemical filters extend the spectral range and ensure a cosmetically elegant texture without white cast.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Comfortable, non-greasy SPF coverage that sits cleanly under makeup. <strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Skin tone begins to even with consistent daily use. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Progressive correction of existing discolouration. <strong>Ongoing:</strong> Prevention of new UV damage and maintained tone correction.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</h3><ol><li>Apply as the final step of your morning skincare routine</li><li>Apply generously — SPF protection is concentration-dependent</li><li>Apply to face, neck, and any exposed skin</li><li>Allow to absorb for 2–3 minutes before applying makeup</li><li>Reapply every 2 hours during prolonged outdoor exposure</li><li>Non-negotiable when using any AHA, retinol, vitamin C, or post-treatment skincare</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>K Complex (Vitamin K + growth factors + repair enzymes)</td><td>Actively corrects discolouration and UV damage while you wear your SPF</td></tr><tr><td>Hybrid mineral/chemical filter system (SPF 50)</td><td>Broad-spectrum UV protection without white cast — elegant texture suitable for all skin tones</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>K Ceutic is the SPF I prescribe to every patient leaving my clinic after a treatment. Sun protection immediately post-treatment is the difference between excellent results and compromised results. What I particularly value about K Ceutic is that it does not just protect — the K Complex continues the correction work started in the clinic every single day the patient wears it. This is a genuinely therapeutic SPF.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I used to avoid SPF because everything felt heavy. K Ceutic absorbs beautifully and my makeup sits perfectly on top.</td><td>After my chemical peel, Dr. Bangalee prescribed this. Three months later my skin tone is more even than it has been in years.</td><td>I wear this every single day. My skin has never looked better and the brown patches I have had for years are noticeably fading.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I wear this under makeup?</td><td>Yes — K Ceutic SPF 50 has a cosmetically elegant texture designed to work under all makeup types. Allow 2–3 minutes to absorb before applying foundation.</td></tr><tr><td>Do I need to reapply during the day?</td><td>For daily indoor or commuting exposure, one morning application is sufficient. For prolonged outdoor exposure, reapply every 2 hours.</td></tr><tr><td>Is K Ceutic suitable for dark skin tones?</td><td>Yes — the hybrid filter system avoids the white cast associated with mineral-only SPF formulations.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat</p><p>Dermaceutic C25 or Tri Vita C30</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Protect</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</p></td></tr></table>', 105000, 105000, true, ARRAY['Dermaceutic', 'K Complex', 'post-treatment', 'recovery cream', 'Restore', 'sensitive skin', 'SPF 50', 'sun protection', 'Vitamin E']),
  ('Dermaceutic Tri Vita C30', 'dermaceutic-tri-vita-c30', 'SA-DERM-PRE-TV-30-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>A single Vitamin C source loses potency within weeks. <strong>Tri Vita C30 uses three distinct Vitamin C forms</strong> — <strong>15% L-Ascorbic Acid, 14.5% Ascorbyl Silanol, and 0.5% Ascorbyl Ester</strong> — each penetrating skin at a different depth and timeframe, ensuring a continuous, layered antioxidant effect across 24 hours. The most comprehensive Vitamin C serum Dermaceutic makes. Evening use. <strong>Not for use during pregnancy.</strong></p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Tri Vita C30 right for you?</h3><ul><li>You want the most advanced Vitamin C formulation available for home use</li><li>You have used C25 and want to progress to a higher-performance option</li><li>Your skin shows established UV damage, pigmentation, or fine lines</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding</li><li>You want a Vitamin C that delivers activity throughout the entire day and night cycle</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Tri Vita C30 works — the science</h3><p>Each form of Vitamin C has a different molecular weight, different skin penetration speed, and different duration of activity. Single-form Vitamin C products create a spike of activity that fades — Tri Vita C30 solves this by using three complementary forms simultaneously.</p><p><strong>L-Ascorbic Acid (15%)</strong> is the most biologically active form — it acts immediately at the skin surface and upper dermis, delivering rapid brightening and antioxidant activity. <strong>Ascorbyl Silanol (14.5%)</strong> is the stable, deeper-penetrating form — it provides sustained activity at the mid-dermis. <strong>Ascorbyl Ester (0.5%)</strong> is the most lipid-soluble form — it penetrates the sebaceous component of the skin and provides prolonged, slow-release activity in the deeper layers. The result: continuous, layered Vitamin C effect across 24 hours.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Skin luminosity visibly improved. Dullness reduced. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Uneven tone and sun damage begin to correct. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Progressive brightening and significant improvement in texture and density. <strong>Ongoing:</strong> Continuous protection against UV and environmental oxidative damage.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Tri Vita C30</h3><ol><li>Apply in the evening — the triple-Vitamin C complex works during the skin''s overnight repair cycle</li><li>Apply after cleansing to clean, dry skin</li><li>A few drops are sufficient — spread evenly across face and neck</li><li>Allow to absorb before applying moisturiser</li><li>Always apply SPF50+ the following morning</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>15% L-Ascorbic Acid</td><td>Most active Vitamin C form — immediate surface brightening and antioxidant activity</td></tr><tr><td>14.5% Ascorbyl Silanol</td><td>Stable mid-dermal Vitamin C — sustained activity that extends the brightening effect</td></tr><tr><td>0.5% Ascorbyl Ester</td><td>Lipid-soluble Vitamin C — deep penetrating, slow-release activity in the sebaceous layer</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Tri Vita C30 represents the evolution of the Vitamin C concept in clinical skincare. The triple-source approach genuinely extends activity across the full 24-hour cycle. I recommend this for patients who have already been on a Vitamin C programme and want to progress, or for those with established UV damage or hyperpigmentation who need a comprehensive anti-pigmentation protocol alongside their in-clinic treatments.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have been using C25 for a year and decided to try Tri Vita C30. The difference is real — my skin is brighter and my pigmentation has faded more in two months on this than in six months on the previous product.</td><td>My skin looks radiant in the morning after using this the night before. Combined with K Ceutic, my skin tone is the most even it has been in my adult life.</td><td>Three months after my pigmentation treatment plus this at home — the result has been transformative.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Is Tri Vita C30 stronger than C25?</td><td>Tri Vita C30 is more comprehensive — higher combined Vitamin C concentration and three complementary forms for layered, continuous activity. C25 is the excellent entry-level clinical Vitamin C; Tri Vita C30 is the advanced protocol.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use this in the morning instead of the evening?</td><td>L-Ascorbic Acid increases UV sensitivity, making morning use less optimal. If you prefer morning Vitamin C, C25 is the better option. For an evening-focused routine, Tri Vita C30 is the premium choice.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Foamer 15</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Tri Vita C30</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic Redens+</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50</p></td></tr></table>', 180000, 180000, true, ARRAY['30% Vitamin C', 'anti-ageing', 'antioxidant', 'brightening', 'Dermaceutic', 'ferulic acid', 'Prevent', 'Vitamin C serum']),
  ('Dermaceutic Yellow Cream', 'dermaceutic-yellow-cream', 'SA-DERM-TAR-YELC-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>For stubborn, localised dark spots that won''t respond to general brightening products, <strong>Yellow Cream is the targeted specialist</strong>. Applied directly to individual marks with a cotton bud, its <strong>5-active depigmenting complex</strong> works at the precise location of the problem — fading existing pigmentation while blocking new melanin from forming. Spot treatment precision. Clinical-grade actives. <strong>Evening use only.</strong> Not for use during pregnancy.</p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Yellow Cream right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have specific, localised dark spots that are not responding to general brightening products</li><li>You want a targeted spot treatment rather than a full-face brightening product</li><li>You have post-blemish marks, age spots, or isolated sun damage in specific areas</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Yellow Cream works — the science</h3><p>Many patients with localised dark spots are already using good general brightening products — but they need spot-specific intervention for their most stubborn marks. Yellow Cream delivers a concentrated <strong>5-active depigmenting complex</strong> applied directly to individual spots with a cotton bud, concentrating clinical-grade actives exactly where they are needed.</p><p>The complex targets multiple stages of melanogenesis simultaneously — inhibiting the enzymes responsible for melanin production, blocking the transfer of melanin to surrounding skin cells, and accelerating the breakdown of existing melanin deposits within the spot. This multi-pathway approach is why Yellow Cream works on spots that single-active products fail to fade.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Targeted spots begin to visibly lighten. Edges of spots become less defined. <strong>Week 4–8:</strong> Progressive fading. Contrast between spot and surrounding skin reducing. <strong>Week 8–12:</strong> Significant correction of treated spots with consistent daily application.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Yellow Cream</h3><ol><li>Apply in the evening only</li><li>After cleansing and any full-face treatments, use a cotton bud to apply Yellow Cream directly to individual dark spots only</li><li>Do not apply to surrounding skin — targeted application maximises efficacy</li><li>Allow to absorb — do not rub or spread</li><li>Apply SPF50+ every morning without exception</li><li>Use consistently every evening for a minimum of 8 weeks on established spots</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>5-active depigmenting complex</td><td>Targets multiple stages of melanin production and transfer — clinical precision that single actives cannot match</td></tr><tr><td>Tyrosinase inhibitor complex</td><td>Blocks the primary enzyme responsible for melanin production at the spot site</td></tr><tr><td>Melanin dispersal actives</td><td>Accelerate the breakdown of existing melanin deposits within treated spots</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Yellow Cream fills a precise gap in the depigmentation toolkit — for patients who have achieved good general tone but have specific stubborn spots not responding to their full-face brightening products. The cotton bud application method ensures maximum concentration exactly at the problem site. I often prescribe Yellow Cream alongside Mela Cream for patients with a mix of diffuse and localised pigmentation.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I had a dark spot on my cheek for three years that nothing would fade. Six weeks of Yellow Cream and it is almost gone. I am genuinely amazed.</td><td>The cotton bud application felt strange at first but I understand why it works — you are putting the full concentration exactly on the problem.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee recommended this for a sun spot on my forehead. Combined with K Ceutic, the spot is 80% faded after two months.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I apply Yellow Cream to a large patch of pigmentation?</td><td>Yellow Cream is designed for localised spots. For large patches of pigmentation or melasma, Mela Cream applied across the full face is more appropriate. Yellow Cream can be used alongside Mela Cream for specific resistant spots.</td></tr><tr><td>How do I apply it correctly?</td><td>Use a clean cotton bud and apply only to the darkened area of each spot. The cream should sit precisely on the spot — not smeared onto surrounding skin.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM (full face)</p><p>Dermaceutic Mela Cream</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Target PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Yellow Cream (spots only)</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 (essential)</p></td></tr></table>', 106000, 106000, true, ARRAY['arbutin', 'dark spot corrector', 'Dermaceutic', 'hyperpigmentation', 'kojic acid', 'licorice', 'melasma', 'PIH', 'Target']),
  ('Dermaceutic Mela Cream', 'dermaceutic-mela-cream', 'SA-DERM-TAR-MELA-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>If dark spots keep returning no matter what you try, the problem is not the spots — it is the cycle producing them. <strong>Mela Cream targets pigmentation at 9 biological stages simultaneously</strong>, blocking melanin production, transfer, and dispersal using a multi-active complex that single-ingredient brighteners cannot match. Evening use only. <strong>Not for use during pregnancy.</strong></p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Mela Cream right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have stubborn dark spots that return after lightening — melasma, sun spots, or post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation</li><li>Single-ingredient brighteners have not delivered the results you want</li><li>You want a comprehensive, multi-pathway approach to persistent pigmentation</li><li>You are committed to daily SPF use alongside your brightening routine</li><li>You are not pregnant or breastfeeding</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Mela Cream works — the science</h3><p>Hyperpigmentation is a multi-step process. UV exposure and hormonal triggers stimulate melanocytes to produce melanin. That melanin is then transferred to surrounding skin cells and distributed through the epidermis — resulting in the dark marks visible at the surface. Treating only one stage of this cascade is why single-ingredient brighteners so often fail.</p><p>Mela Cream disrupts pigmentation at <strong>9 biological stages simultaneously</strong> — blocking melanin production, inhibiting its transfer, and accelerating its dispersal from skin cells. The multi-active complex includes clinically validated brightening actives targeting different points in the melanogenesis pathway, ensuring comprehensive disruption even when individual pathways show partial resistance.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Existing dark spots begin to lighten. New spot formation visibly reduced. <strong>Week 4–8:</strong> Progressive fading of established pigmentation. Skin tone beginning to even. <strong>Week 8–12:</strong> Significant improvement in overall skin tone uniformity. <strong>Ongoing:</strong> Continued correction with maintenance use — SPF is essential to prevent new formation.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Mela Cream</h3><ol><li>Apply in the evening only</li><li>After cleansing, apply a thin, even layer across the entire face</li><li>Allow to absorb before applying moisturiser if needed</li><li>Apply SPF50+ (K Ceutic) every morning without exception</li><li>Introduce gradually — begin 3 evenings per week and increase to nightly as tolerated</li><li>Typical course length: 3–6 months for established pigmentation</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>9-stage multi-active brightening complex</td><td>Disrupts melanin production, transfer, and dispersal simultaneously — addresses pigmentation where single actives fail</td></tr><tr><td>Tyrosinase inhibitors (multiple)</td><td>Block the enzyme responsible for converting tyrosine to melanin — the primary rate-limiting step in pigmentation</td></tr><tr><td>Melanin transfer inhibitors</td><td>Prevent melanosomes from moving from pigment cells to surrounding skin cells</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Melasma and persistent hyperpigmentation require intervention at multiple points simultaneously. Mela Cream is the home-care product I recommend for patients who are serious about correcting established pigmentation, always in combination with daily SPF and, where appropriate, in-clinic treatments such as Dermapen or chemical peels. Consistent evening use for 3–6 months, never missing SPF, and we typically see remarkable results.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have had melasma for six years and tried everything. Three months on Mela Cream with K Ceutic SPF in the morning and the difference is genuinely dramatic.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee prescribed this after my pigmentation treatment. The combination has cleared spots I had given up on completely.</td><td>The key is consistency and never missing the SPF. With both products, my skin tone has been the most even it has been in a decade.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>How long do I need to use Mela Cream?</td><td>For mild hyperpigmentation, improvement is often visible within 4 weeks. For established melasma, 8–12 weeks of consistent use is typically required.</td></tr><tr><td>Will my dark spots come back after I stop?</td><td>Pigmentation can recur when triggering factors (UV, hormonal) are present. The SPF is what prevents recurrence — Mela Cream corrects; SPF prevents.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use Mela Cream with in-clinic treatments?</td><td>Yes — Mela Cream works synergistically with in-clinic pigmentation treatments. Dr. Bangalee typically combines clinic treatments with Mela Cream home care for optimal lasting results.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser or Foamer 15</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat PM</p><p>Dermaceutic Mela Cream</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic (if needed)</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect AM</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 (essential)</p></td></tr></table>', 211000, 211000, true, ARRAY['acne marks', 'dark spots', 'Dermaceutic', 'mandelic acid', 'melasma', 'niacinamide', 'pigmentation cream', 'salicylic acid', 'Target']),
  ('Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic Redens', 'dermaceutic-hyal-ceutic-redens', 'SA-DERM-STI-HCR-001', 'dermaceutic', '<p>As skin ages it loses density — not just moisture on the surface, but the structural fullness underneath that makes it look firm and plump. <strong>Hyal Ceutic Redens+ targets this precisely</strong> with <strong>triple-weight Hyaluronic Acid</strong>, a patented <strong>SENEB molecular zone</strong> that repairs the skin''s density matrix, and ceramides for barrier reinforcement. This is deep moisturisation at a structural level — for skin that has started to feel thinner, looser, or less resilient.</p>', '<h3>Is Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic Redens+ right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin has started to feel thinner, looser, or less resilient</li><li>You notice your skin lacks the plumpness and firmness it once had</li><li>Fine lines appear more prominent when skin is dry</li><li>Standard moisturisers hydrate the surface but do not address loss of structural density</li><li>You want a clinically-formulated alternative to cosmetic density treatments</li></ul><h3>How Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic Redens+ works — the science</h3><p>Skin density loss is distinct from surface dehydration. As we age, the extracellular matrix — the structural scaffolding that gives skin its firmness — undergoes degradation. Hyaluronic Acid in the dermis decreases, the matrix proteins that hold moisture in place become disorganised, and the skin''s natural density zones become thinner. The result is skin that looks less full, less firm, and less resilient.</p><p>Hyal Ceutic Redens+ addresses this at three levels simultaneously. The <strong>triple-weight Hyaluronic Acid system</strong> (ultra-low, low, and high molecular weight) hydrates at the surface, mid-dermis, and deep dermal layer — creating genuine three-dimensional moisture density. The patented <strong>SENEB molecular zone technology</strong> acts directly on the extracellular matrix, reinforcing the structural framework that supports skin density. <strong>Ceramides</strong> reinforce the skin barrier, preventing moisture loss and protecting the density gains achieved by the active complex.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Skin feels visibly more comfortable and plump. <strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Surface dryness resolved; skin appears more luminous. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Fine lines appear less pronounced. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Ongoing improvement in skin firmness and density — results compound with continued use.</p><h3>How to use Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic Redens+</h3><ol><li>Apply morning and evening after cleansing and any treatment serums</li><li>Warm a small amount between fingertips</li><li>Press gently into face, neck, and décolleté using upward lifting motions</li><li>Do not pull or drag the skin — gentle pressing maximises absorption</li><li>Follow with SPF in the morning</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Triple-weight Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Hydrates at surface, mid-dermis and deep dermal levels — genuine structural moisture density</td></tr><tr><td>SENEB Molecular Zone (patented)</td><td>Reinforces extracellular matrix to restore and maintain the structural density of ageing skin</td></tr><tr><td>Ceramides</td><td>Rebuild and strengthen the skin barrier to seal in moisture and protect structural gains</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee''s clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Hyal Ceutic Redens+ bridges the gap between cosmetic moisturisers and clinical density treatments. For patients who feel their skin has become thinner and less resilient, this is the moisturiser that addresses the actual underlying change, not just the surface symptom. I typically pair it with Tri Vita C30 or C25 in the morning to deliver both density support and antioxidant protection simultaneously.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have tried every premium moisturiser and this is the first one that has actually made a difference to the firmness of my skin. It absorbs beautifully.</td><td>Within six weeks my skin looks noticeably fuller and the lines around my mouth appear less deep. I was not expecting this from a moisturiser.</td><td>The difference in my skin density after two months is visible in photographs. Remarkable result from a moisturiser.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>How is Hyal Ceutic Redens+ different from Hyal Ceutic?</td><td>Hyal Ceutic is the lightweight daily hydrator for oily and combination skin. Redens+ is richer, for skin that has lost structural density — typically drier, more mature skin. Redens+ also contains the patented SENEB complex which targets the extracellular matrix.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use Hyal Ceutic Redens+ with retinol?</td><td>Yes — Redens+ is an excellent partner for retinol use. Apply retinol first (wait 15 minutes), then apply Redens+. The ceramide complex provides barrier support that enhances retinol tolerance.</td></tr><tr><td>Does it work for neck and décolleté?</td><td>Yes — apply with gentle pressing motions working upward from décolleté to jawline.</td></tr></table><h3>Complete your routine</h3><table><tr><td><p>Step 1 — Cleanse</p><p>Dermaceutic Advanced Cleanser</p></td><td><p>Step 2 — Treat</p><p>Dermaceutic C25 or Tri Vita C30 (morning) / Activ Retinol (evening)</p></td><td><p>Step 3 — Moisturise</p><p>Dermaceutic Hyal Ceutic Redens+</p></td><td><p>Step 4 — Protect</p><p>Dermaceutic K Ceutic SPF 50 (morning)</p></td></tr></table>', 130000, 130000, true, ARRAY['anti-ageing', 'Dermaceutic', 'fine lines', 'hyaluronic acid', 'plumping cream', 'Stimulate', 'volume', 'wrinkles'])
on conflict (slug) do update set
  name               = excluded.name,
  sku                = excluded.sku,
  short_description  = excluded.short_description,
  description        = excluded.description,
  price_cents        = excluded.price_cents,
  regular_price_cents = excluded.regular_price_cents,
  tags               = excluded.tags,
  updated_at         = now();

